4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO WATERCRAFT; ALLOWING
5 NIGHTTIME OPERATION OF MOTORBOATS OR VESSELS TOWING PERSONS ENGAGED IN
6 WATERSKIING OR RELATED ACTIVITIES; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; PROVIDING AN
7 APPROPRIATION; AND AMENDING SECTION 23-2-529, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 23-2-529, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "23-2-529. Waterskis, and surfboards, and similar devices. (1) A person may not operate a
13 motorboat or vessel on any waters of this state for the purpose of towing a person or persons on waterskis, a
14 surfboard, or similar device unless the operator is accompanied by an observer. If the operator is 12 years of
15 age or younger, there must be a second person, at least 18 years of age, in the vessel to observe the person
16 being towed. The fish and wildlife commission shall adopt rules regarding the proper observation and safe
17 towing of persons on waterskis or similar devices, based on density of use of a body of water.
18 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (2)(b), A a person may not operate a motorboat or vessel
19 towing a person engaged in waterskiing, surfboarding, or similar activity or towing some other contrivances nor
20 may a person engage in those activities at any time between the hours from sunset to sunrise., except that
21 (b) this The provisions of subsection (2)(a) does do not apply to:
22 (i) a motorboat or vessel that is towing at 15 miles an hour or less one or more persons on
23 waterskis, a surfboard, a foilboard, or a similar device that properly illuminates the vessel and the person being
24 towed, as determined by rules adopted by the fish and wildlife commission; or
25 (ii) a performer engaged in a professional exhibition or a person engaged in a regatta or race
26 authorized under this part.
27 (3) All right-of-way rules applying to a towing vessel apply to a person being towed."
